Project.Title: Proteomic study of the transition to stationary phase in halorchaea Natrialba magadii and Haloferax volcanii
Project.Description: A high throughput proteomics approach was used to analyze and compare the proteome of two halophilic archaea (Haloferax volcanii and Natrialba magadii) during exponential and stationary growth.

Relation.Keywords: label-free shotgun proteomics, Natrialba magadii, Haloferax volcanii, stationary phase, Archaea

PubMed.PubMedInfo: Cerletti M, Giménez MI, Tröetschel C, D' Alessandro C, Poetsch A, De Castro RE, Paggi RA Proteomic Study of the Exponential-Stationary Growth Phase Transition in the Haloarchaea Natrialba magadii and Haloferax volcanii. Proteomics. 2018 Jul;18(14):e1800116
